Environmentalists advocate for reducing emissions and transitioning to renewable energy sources to combat global warming.
They acknowledge that this won't completely solve the issue but believe it's crucial to act swiftly.
The focus is on capturing and storing carbon dioxide to prevent further emissions.
Britain is exploring carbon capture technology to cut emissions by 60% by 2050.
The G8 recognizes climate change as a serious challenge and emphasizes the need for cooperation.
The US faces criticism for not ratifying environmental treaties.
Scientists suggest storing carbon dioxide underground as a temporary solution while cleaner technologies are developed.
The urgency to address carbon emissions is highlighted as the world faces increasing levels of CO2 production
